{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"PASS-1 REVIEW [T1 prior-art / novel-architecture justification] on \"Repo-snapshot isolation for code-reading gates\": CLEAN — no findings. T1 bright-lines fire (novel snapshot-materialization architecture; security/auth via HMAC-signed attestation + private-repo credentials; concurrency/scalability target), and the plan engages the criterion well. AFFIRMATIONS — (a) prior art considered: the Design paragraph names six relevant systems (GitLab Gitaly, Sourcegraph gitserver/zoekt, GitHub tarball API, Bazel, ccache, Nix, in-toto) and maps concrete choices to them (\"read content from the object store without a worktree; pin an immutable SHA; reaper + free-space cap … match what those systems ship\"); (b) novelty justified / anti-repackaging: the plan deliberately does NOT claim novelty — it positions its core mechanics as matching established practice, and the single deviation (\"drop the PID lease; use kernel guarantees\") is justified by a spike rather than asserted; (c) capability assertions: the one genuinely platform-risky assertion (EFS/NFS flock semantics) is surfaced and responsibly scoped out to alto-fruit-punch rather than silently assumed."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782519579909280001,"uuid":"9aaf571a-b174-4ae4-835b-59c4a27615c8"}